Fredrick Ade Ogidan, has assumed duty as the new Sector Commander of the Federal Road Safety Commission, FRSC, in Kwara State. This followed the promotion and subsequent posting of the former Sector Commander, Jonathan Owoade, to Zone 6, Port Harcourt, Rivers State. Until his new appointment, Fredrick Ogidan, was the Kaduna state Sectorâ€™s Head of Operations. At his maiden meeting with staff of the Kwara Sector, Fredrick promised to work with the entire staff in creating a safe motoring environment in the state. Similarly, he will soon embark on familiarisation visits to sister agencies and critical stakeholders after the Eidel-Fitr celebrations, according to a statement by the Chief Route Commander, Special Patrol Operations, Dapo James, in Ilorin on Wednesday.